DESCRIPTION Do you want to help build a highly personalized homepage that greets each of our millions of customers worldwide every time they visit Amazon.com? Are you interested in building data pipelines that process petabytes of customer behavior data? Amazon's Homepage Personalization team develops ,supports personalization ,recommendations for Amazon customers across music, books, movies, fashion, ,everything else that Amazon offers. We analyze petabytes of implicit ,explicit feedback data on our hundreds of millions of customers ,billions of products in order to guide the development of a meaningful ,highly personalized homepage experience. We are looking for an experienced ,forward thinking software engineer with a focus on data engineering to join our team. This person will work closely with other software engineers ,machine learning scientists to design ,implement predictive, scalable models for everything from product recommendations to personalized mobile content layouts. You will work directly with machine learning scientists to scale up collaborative filtering models on retail purchases, Prime Video views, Prime Music streams, ,other Amazon data to deeply underst,our customers. This is one of the foremost roles in data engineering with the opportunity to reach millions of customers on one of the highest traffic consumer websites in the world. If you are passionate about data engineering, software engineering ,personalization at scale then we encourage you to apply. BASIC QUALIFICATIONS - BS or MS degree in computer science or related field. - Strong coding experience, preferably with Scala, Python, Java, or C++. - Strong grasp of data structures ,algorithms. - Ability to explain complex issues in technical ,non-technical terms. - Cares deeply about agile software practices, data driven development, ,collaborating with other engineers ,researchers. - Working knowledge of Hadoop, Spark, Redshift, DynamoDB, Kinesis, or other big data technologies. PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS - Experience with supervised ,unsupervised machine learning models. - Experience with collaborative filtering ,recommender systems. - Experience running ,evaluating AB Tests.

Global FBA is looking for a passionate, talented product manager to develop pricing recommendations for the global business. The ideal candidate has outstanding business acumen ,judgment, intense curiosity, excellent analytical abilities, strong technical skills, superior written ,verbal communication skills, ,the ability to influence cross-functional teams. He/she will have a strong bias toward data driven decision making. He/she will be a self-starter, comfortable with ambiguity ,juggling multiple projects, able to think big ,be creative (while paying careful attention to detail), ,will enjoy working in a fast-paced dynamic environment. He/she will work closely with Marketing, Operations, ,Finance teams around the world. The scope for this role includes the following: Identify, develop, manage, ,execute analyses to uncover areas of opportunity ,present written business recommendations that will help shape the future of FBA. Drive development of quantitative models necessary for the evaluation ,implementation of new pricing strategies. Collaborate with product managers to develop pricing recommendations for new features or services. Manage fee development ,implementation, including long term project planning ,development resource allocation. Report key insights ,trends, using statistical rigor to simplify ,inform the larger team of noteworthy story lines. Collaborate with finance ,product management as a leader of quantitative analysis. Analyze ,solve business problems at their root, stepping back to underst,the broader context. Develop solutions that utilize the highest standards of analytical rigor ,data integrity. Recognize ,adopt best practices in reporting ,analysis: data integrity, test design, analysis, validation, ,documentation. Write high quality SQL code to retrieve ,analyze data. Learn ,underst,a broad range of Amazon's data resources ,know how, when, ,which to use. Manage ,execute entire projects or components of large projects from start to finish including project management, data gathering ,manipulation, synthesis ,modeling, problem solving, ,communication of insights ,recommendations. Build scalable database solutions when required. Participate in periodic reviews with Amazon Executive Leadership team. FBA leverages Amazon's global fulfillment ,customer service network for third party sellers who want to grow their business on ,off Amazon.com. FBA enables customers to take advantage of Free Super Saver Shipping ,Amazon Prime on third party items, while sellers can focus on selling rather than shipping. The Sr. Product Manager will be responsible for driving analysis in an effort to improve our understanding of Seller's costs globally. The role is global in scope ,includes strategy, analysis ,execution for FBA in North America, Europe ,Asia.
